Package com.epoch.mechanisms

Classes for holding and analyzing mechanisms.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Mechanism
    Wraps a response mechanism, and includes methods for analyzing its validity.
    MechArrow
    Describes a straight arrow (reaction or resonance) connecting two stages of a mechanism.
    MechFlow
    Describes an electron-flow arrow.
    MechParser
    Extracts data from MRV of a response mechanism, parses and orders the stages.
    MechRuleFunctions
    Analyzes mechanisms for violations of heuristic rules.
    MechSet
    Compares sets of molecules for mechanisms.
    MechSolver
    Calculates products of molecules and electron-flow arrows.
    MechStage
    Contains data and references to items inside a rectangle (box, stage).
    MechSubstructSearch
    Searches for a structure and associated electron-flow arrows in a stage.
    MechUtils
    Methods for coloring mechanism components.
    MechValidFlows
    Analyzes the validity of a mechanism.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MechError
    Contains the results of a failure of a mechanism operation.
    MechFormatException
    Thrown when a malformed mechanism found in a "valid" marvin document.
